  "descriptionShort": "World trade index, based on the average of exports and imports values, adjusted for inflation (1800 = 1).",
  "descriptionProcessing": "We combined historical trade data from Federico & Tena-Junguito (2016) (up to 1950) with World Trade Organization (WTO) data (from 1951 onwards). We re-indexed the Federico & Tena-Junguito series, originally expressed relative to 1913 = 100, so that 1800 = 1. We then rescaled the WTO index, originally set to 1950 = 100, using the 1950 overlap to align it with this 1800 = 1 scale. This ensures both series are presented consistently on the same baseline.",
